<title type="html"><![CDATA[HDMA problem]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6439&amp;p=62157#p62157"><![CDATA[
I'm having trouble with the 3d ocean effect in the background of my game.  It scrolls at different speeds depending on how many sprite patterns are being DMAed per frame.  I'm guessing the 3d scrolling speed depends on what scanline the HDMA starts with, since the farther down scanlines scroll faster than the scanlines above (hence the 3d effect).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4383">psycopathicteen</a> — Sun May 30, 2010 7:35 pm</p><hr />
